               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was in Thames-street, a man asked me to go and get a piece of cord to tie up come thing, and he would give me half—crown for half a day's work—he gave me the crown piece—I went and asked for a small rope-be said he had not got one—he said he could cat me one—I was considering how long to have it—I told him about twelve yards—he cut it me—I took the halfpence out to give him the crown piece—he said it was a bad one—I said I would go back to the man I had it of.</p>
